'''Pavlos Beligratis''' ({{lang-el|Παύλος Μπελιγράτης}}; born November 16, 1977 in [[Athens]]) is a Greek beach volleyball player.<ref name="SR">{{cite sports-reference|Pavlos Beligratis|https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/be/pavlos-beligratis-1.html|3 May 2014}}</ref>

Beligratis competed at the [[FIVB Beach Volleyball World Tour]] between 2000 and 2005.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pavlos Beligratis Season Summaries 1999-2005|url=http://www.bvbinfo.com/player.asp?ID=2107&Page=3#2000FIVB%20C&S|publisher=Beach Volleyball Database|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref> In 2004 he qualified to the [[2004 Summer Olympics|Summer Olympics]] in his hometown, Athens, alongside [[Athanasios Michalopoulos]]. During the match against the South Africans [[Colin Pocock]] and [[Gershon Rorich]], Beligratis suffered an injury in his right leg and was forced withdraw from the Olympics before the last group stage match against [[Mariano Baracetti]] and [[Martin Conde]], from Argentina.<ref>{{cite web|title=Greek pair withdraws from beach tournament|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/espn/wire?section=oly&id=1861859|date=18 August 2004|publisher=[[ESPN]]|accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref>

